\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From those theorems above, we can see extended Borel–Cantelli lemmas can
 relax parts of the assumptions in the original one such as independence.
 However, the drawback is obvious that we either need some more complicated
 conditions or can only get some weaker results.
 The beauty in the original Borel–Cantelli lemma's simplicity and interpretabili
ty is lost.
 Many of those theorem are derived as lemmas for varied purposes or specified
 problems.
 Although it seems that most of those lemmas are more general, they're not
 as popular as the original one because those extended lemmas are more difficult
 to explain and remember.
\end_layout

